<br>
It was fun wasn't it. One person can make a difference. If we all just make the small effort of contacting one newspaper, one radio station or send one letter to congress it can make a big impact. Like ripples in a pond it spreads and changes everything a little. I wonder how many people were listening to that show. The phone caller asking for secrecy was just a concerned citizen who doesn't realise much of the science is already kept under wraps and has been classified since the forties. Ignorance is what we are fighting against. GNAWNPIS is just a figurehead for ignorance. We can captivate an audience with the wonder of space travel just as our opposition can frighten them with lies. If we keep on sprinkling some of the truth into our speaches people will slowly become more informed. Thats the hope. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cotopaxi@nuclearspace>cotopaxi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/5/03 7:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=759.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  Phoned into C-span this morning talk with Roald Gagdeev </span><hr size=1> Bro... It was Ok, just too early in the morning for me.<br>
<br>
